<b>Floyd</b> | Bonehead is the mostly true story of Fred Merkle, major league baseball
<b>Floyd</b> | player for the New York Giants, and the mistake he made as a teenager
<b>Floyd</b> | that haunted him for the rest of his life.  There are some puzzles, but
<b>Floyd</b> | the primary emphasis is on setting and story.  Poking around is
<b>Floyd</b> | strongly encouraged.  Although it is possible to put the game in an
<b>Floyd</b> | unwinnable state, it will become painfully obvious within two or three
<b>Floyd</b> | moves that this has happened.  With a few UNDOs, you should always be
<b>Floyd</b> | able to get to a final (if not exactly winning) ending.  Needless to
<b>Floyd</b> | say, saving the game from time to time, especially once you're at the
<b>Floyd</b> | ballpark, is recommended.
<b>Floyd</b> |
<b>Floyd</b> | The game features a great deal of baseball-related activity and
<b>Floyd</b> | language, some of it antiquated.  If you are unfamiliar with baseball,
<b>Floyd</b> | you will doubtless be somewhat confused at times, but I have tried to
<b>Floyd</b> | make the game as forgiving to novices as possible.  See Baseball in
<b>Floyd</b> | Three Paragraphs in this menu for some basic information on the sport.
<b>Floyd</b> | Also, be sure to talk to everyone you can talk to, especially a certain
<b>Floyd</b> | right fielder on your team, and you will eventually learn what a
<b>Floyd</b> | ballplayer needs to know.
<b>Floyd</b> |
<b>Floyd</b> | Normal movement using compass directions is supplemented with GO TO
<b>Floyd</b> | &lt;location&gt;.  You may find this handy when moving around the diamond.
<b>Floyd</b> |
<b>Floyd</b> | Conversation is handled using Eric Eve's terrific Conversation
<b>Floyd</b> | Framework and Conversation Suggestions.  To initiate a conversation
<b>Floyd</b> | with a character, you can TALK TO the character, or SAY HELLO TO him,
<b>Floyd</b> | or ASK him ABOUT or TELL him ABOUT something.  Use TOPICS to display
<b>Floyd</b> | conversation topics.  Occasionally a character might respond to
<b>Floyd</b> | something not in his topics list.  You may also be able to REMEMBER
<b>Floyd</b> | advice that other characters have given you previously.
<b>Floyd</b> |
<b>Floyd</b> | From time to time the game will display images at the top of the
<b>Floyd</b> | screen.  Having a reasonably large window size may be helpful.  Note
